{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #217: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. For which $n$ are there $n$ points in $\\mathbb{R}^2$, no three on a line and no four on a circle, which determine $n-1$ distinct distances and so that (in some ordering of the distances) the $i$th distance occurs $i$ times? Current best: Erd\\H{o}s originally believed this was impossible for $n\\geq 5$, but Pomerance constructed a set with $n=5$ (see \\cite{Er83c} for a description), and Pal\\'{a}sti has proved such sets exist for all $n\\leq 8$. Prize: no. Tags: distances, geometry.","id":"vf_6c79f9c2156124eb","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: FC 217 (PR #4064) [in-pr] https://github.com/google-deepmind/formal-conjectures/pull/4064.","id":"vf_8148c98f24c77dce","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/217.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_6c79f9c2156124eb","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:217","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_8148c98f24c77dce","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:217","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_8148c98f24c77dce","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"vf_6c79f9c2156124eb","trust":"signed"}],"external_references":[],"formal_conjectures_activity":null,"frontier_id":"vfr_0a25edabc16db143